02/04/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met with several officials Thursday (1 April) during his visit to Washington. He discussed programme co-operation with USAID Administrator Andrew S. Natsios, who praised the "considerable progress" Albania has made in improving its economic indicators. Nano also met with Attorney General John Ashcroft, with whom he discussed measures against the financing of global terrorism, and with CIA Director George Tenet, who pledged CIA assistance to Albania's secret services. (ATA - 01/04/04)
